        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=19515&TOPIC_ID=2494&FORUM_ID=3&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&Topic_Title=SD+Guide+%28Illustrated%21%21%29&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Hey.</P><P>Excellent guide.  If this had been about last week, I coulda saved myself a great deal of pain, in figuring out for myself.  <i>(I started out by trying to pull from 10 and 11.  This results in 10, 11 and 12 all being rather less than pleased and tearing big chunks outta my hide!)</i></P><P>What is worth adding, is that there are two spawns at 5.  One stands upon the broken wall and one beneath.  These two in particular are a pain in the ass to single pull.  To do it, you have to stand directly north and tag the closest one.  Then you can run him around the edge of the plateau.  If you're not directly North, he brings his buddy along.  Having said which, if you're pulling with Darkness and it stuck, you can just run his friend to your pet and hunt him.  The Darkened one will drop out of aggro range and can be hunted afterwards.</P><P>Since I'm only L52, my spell line-up is a little different:<BR>1.  Engulfing Darkness.<BR>2.  Bond of Death.<BR>3.  Plague.<BR>4.  Splurt.<BR>5.  Envenomed Bolt.<BR>6.  Dread of Night.<BR>7.  Feign Death.<BR>8.  Steelskin.  (Switching with Shield, Lich and DMF, for refreshes.)</P><P>I pull with Darkness and, (assuming it stuck,) put Splurt on, while returning to my pet.  I normally only use either Plague, or Envenomed Bolt, rather than both.  This works fine and dandy and the only thing that has a habit of resisting is Darkness.</P><P>What I am curious about, is how many HPs the revenants have.  I'm not entirely sure whether I'm successfully outdamaging my pet, or not.  I guess I'll have to DoT one without the pet and see how far he sinks.</P><P>Anyhow, great guide.  And the diagram for the pulling sequence is excellent.</P><P>AlAaraaf.</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

